text=(:nogroupheader:)%0a(:Summary::)%0a(:Published::)%0a(:Author:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:License:[[https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Res_communis|Site License]]:)%0a(:Update::)%0a(:Maintainer:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:Creator:[[]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!Cryptics]]:)%0a(:Also:none:)%0a(:Archive:[[|Archive.is]], [[|Archive.org]]:)%0a(:Download:[[{$FullName}?action=print|URL]],[[https://www.web2pdfconvert.com/|PDF from URL]]:)%0a%0aSee also [[Ergon Fork]], [[Beetcoin]], [[staticcoin]], [[Randomx]], [[Blockchain design]], [[Blockvault]], [[Doge fork]], [[PoW]]%0a%0aBased on Ergon%0a%0aCodename Perfectcoin or cpuergon%0a%0amonero uncertainties [[https://youtu.be/X_waXHRovbE|#]]%0a%0a!!Technicals%0a%0aBlocktime 12 seconds, low enough to allow fast transactions, high enough to accommodate large blocksizes in the future while keeping it decentralized.  12 seconds was proven viable by ethereum.%0a%0aEmission initially calibrated so a median or mean miner would produce 1 coin per hour.%0a%0a3 decimals%0a%0a"Difficulty" doubles every 2.6 years which is never changed (see [[#koomey|Koomey's Law]])%0a%0aUses [[Randomx#xd|RandomXD]] algorithm which is optimized for servers and gaming PC's and stays out of reach of GPU's (and asics)%0a%0aTx minimum fee 0.1 coins per kb.  Since you can probably mine 1 coin per hour on your gaming PC, you could make one 10kb transaction [[ https://www.getmonero.org/2017/12/11/A-note-on-fees.html|#]]  per hour for "free".%0a%0aDynamic blocksize just like Monero.%0a%0aCoinbase maturity of 2 weeks to prevent pool hopping and disincentivize commercial pools. %0a%0aDifficulty adjustment time either same as monero [[ https://monero.stackexchange.com/questions/7975/how-does-the-difficulty-adjustment-for-monero-work|#]] [[https://www.reddit.com/r/Monero/comments/8ae506/question_about_the_difficulty/|#]]  or ergon as required.%0a%0a!!!RandomX changes%0a%0a# No Light Mode%0a%0a# Memory scaling with moores law%0a%0a# Start memory req at upper mid level CPU like Ryzen 7.%0a%0a*In 2022 L1 should be 32 kb, L2 should be 512 kb, L3 should be 4mb, dataset should be 8GB (adjusted for moores law since 2019) [[https://github.com/tevador/RandomX/blob/master/doc/design.md#14-memory-hardness|#]] [[https://github.com/tevador/RandomX/blob/master/doc/configuration.md|#]]%0a%0a*However the above is based on extrapolating current randomx settings.  Since scratchpads were designed solely to fit within Cache [[https://github.com/tevador/RandomX/blob/master/doc/design.md#28-scratchpad|#]], we can try to utilize the entire cache.  Better settings could be based on current ryzen 7 which would be L1: 512kb, L2: 8mb, L3:32 mb, dataset:8GB? [[https://github.com/tevador/RandomX/blob/master/doc/design.md#28-scratchpad|#]] [[https://www.amd.com/en/products/cpu/amd-ryzen-7-7700x|#]]%0a%0a!!!TLDR%0a%0a*Cpu only%0a%0a*More coins, only 3 decimals%0a%0a*Fast confirmations%0a%0a*Proportional rewards%0a%0a*Privacy%0a%0a*Dynamic blocksize%0a%0a*Low transaction fee%0a%0a*Less pools, no botnets%0a%0a!!Adjusting for Koomey's law [[#koomey]]%0a%0aKoomeys law which is the efficiency growth over time gives a doubling time every 1.57 years for the first 50 years then slowed to doubling every 2.6 years after that.%0a%0aPick 2.6 year doubling time which would slightly always overestimate koomeys law meaning coins/kwh will always very slowly go down.%0a%0aa of 0.99 for slight damping.%0a%0aIf koomey's law ever fails and processors stop developing altogether and you can only get old processors (all processor production stops), cpuergon would experience a bitcoin-like halving every 2.6 years. %0a%0a!!"Roadmap"%0a%0aI put this in quotes to denote there is no set time schedule nor a set plan and this is open to debate and change.  This is basically my own personal wishlist.  Also I am not a good enough coder to know how to code implementations of these in many cases.%0a%0a#Every year reassess CPU-only traits of the algorithm.  Increase memory hardness and/or requirement as needed so the largest graphics card on the market does not have enough memory to mine [[Randomx#config|See RandomXD]].  If these sorts of hardforks are not scheduled on a set time frame, chances are they won't happen or will stop happening, so they must be scheduled on a set time frame (if I didn't make myself obvious).  High memory requirement will also restrict botnets.%0a%0a#Restrict pools either by what wownero did or preferably including signing instead of hashing for the hashing process.  Small pool friendliness could be implemented by saying we need 1%25 of the coinbase outputs to sign each hash. This means to mine you need the private key(s) of 1%25 of the coinbase outputs.  This also prevents botnets, and prevents other forms of miners from being subservient to pools.  The reasoning behind pool unfriendliness is that the miners within each pool do not contribute at all to decentralization and are thus wasted power use.  Only the number pools (or solo miners) contribute to decentralization so we want as many solo miners / small pools as possible.%0a%0a#Restrict speculative mining (hashrate swings) by making a long coinbase maturity (on the order of months).  This also will help restrict pools and even botnets.%0a%0a#Improve asic resistance by including hashing/signing an entire block as part of the hashing process.  Since we have dynamic blocksize increases (or no blocksize limit at all?), this will improve memory hardness substantially.%0a%0a#Difficulty adjustment every block if possible.%0a%0a#Make faucet and tipbot and create a donation address that goes to faucet and funds grants to people to do giveaways, tipping, or development (not restricted to this coin only).%0a%0a#Create decentralized trading pairs for cpuergon/ergon, cpuergon/monero, cpuergon/bitcoincash, cpuergon/dogecoin, cpuergon/litecoin, cpuergon/ravencoin, cpuergon/bitcoin.  I will not "apply" to an exchange to have them list the coin.  If someone else wants to or the exchange wants to list the coin itself, they are free to do so.  This is mainly because of privacy concerns.%0a%0a#Afaik tokens and NFT's and other functionalities that require a transparent blockchain would not be viable on cpuergon.  For these use cases use Ergon.%0a%0a#Transaction fee waiver using profun work [[https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=5377322.0|#]] which means you can "mine" for your transaction fees offline individually without needing a pool to win a block.
